## Scenario 2: Critical Issue During Flow

**Owner:** "now add the refresh token"

**Builder:**

Hold — storing refresh tokens in localStorage is XSS-vulnerable. HttpOnly cookie + secure flag applied. Go.

```typescript
// Changed in src/routes/auth.ts
router.post('/login', async (req, res) => {
  // (email/password validation same as Scenario 1)
  const accessToken = createToken({ id: user.id, email: user.email });
  const refreshToken = createRefreshToken(user.id);
  
  // Store refresh in HttpOnly cookie
  res.cookie('refreshToken', refreshToken, {
    httpOnly: true,
    secure: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production',
    sameSite: 'strict',
    maxAge: 7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000 // 7 days
  });
  
  res.json({ accessToken, user: { id: user.id, email: user.email } });
});
```
✓

